Norwegian oil group Statoil said that it had to resume production on two of its platforms after a gas leak forced it to shut down operations earlier this week, cutting Norway's total oil output by 200,000 barrels per day.
Norwegian North Sea oil platform being evacuated after gas leak.
Norway is the world's third-largest oil exporter after Saudi Arabia and Russia.
A team of about 60 workers is trying to seal the leak with cement.
